<h4>Exposé</h4>
<div class='textile space-l'><p>Arena Romanistica: Journal of Romance studies</p>
<p>Arena Romanistica is an international peer-reviewed journal published by the Department of Foreign Languages, University of Bergen. The journal is devoted to Romance studies, embracing philological, linguistic, literary and cultural research.</p>
<p>Arena Romanistica was founded in 2005. It is a biannual publication, each issue being dedicated to an announced theme as well as an open section.</p>
<p>Arena Romanistica holds a high academic standard. This quality is guaranteed by our distinguished scientific committee. It is our policy to maintain an international profile with respect to both contributions and peer-reviewing.</p>
<p>The journal has been categorized as a scientific publication of &#8220;level 1&#8221; by The Norwegian Association of Higher Education Institutions (<a href="http://www.uhr.no" target="_blank">http://www.uhr.no</a>).</p></div>
<h4>Inhalt</h4>
<div class='textile'><p>Table of contents:</p>
<p>Pablo Brescia, University of South Florida: Short Story Theory: The View From Latin America</p>
<p>Milagro Martín Clavijo, Universidad de Salamanca: Indemoniate de G. Musso y C. Tolazzi: estudio antropológico sobre las mujeres alpinas del siglo <span class="caps">XIX</span></p>
<p>Jean-Louis Cornille, University of Cape Town (<span class="caps">UCT</span>): Genèse d’un mauvais genre : la pose du poème en prose baudelairien</p>
<p>Marilena De Chiara, Universitat Pompeu Fabra: La scena nel testo: Enrico IV di Luigi Pirandello</p>
<p>Eva Maria Loos, Ruprecht-Karls-Universität Heidelberg: El concepto de género en el contexto de los medios de comunicación</p>
<p>Miriam López Santos, Universidad de León: El género gótico. ¿Génesis de la literatura fantástica?</p>
<p>Anne-Céline Michel, Université de Poitiers: Le genre des Nuits chez Alfred de Musset, une poétique de refonte des codes</p>
<p>Maria Belén Hernández González, Universidad de Murcia: La fortuna literaria de Goliarda Sapienza</p>
<p>Juan Carlos Palazuelos, Universidad Adolfo Ibáñez: ¿Que es un ensayo?Un problema y una solucíon para la didática de la lengua en español</p>
<p>Linda Pennings, Universiteit van Amsterdam: I generi letterari nell’estetica crociana, fra tradizione e attualità</p>
<p>Enrico Santangelo, Independent researcher: &#8220;Reliqua cogitando percipies&#8221;: Dante in Petrarch’s Bucolicum carmen I (Parthenias)</p>
<p>Iuliana Savu, Universitatea Alexandru Ioan Cuza: Gen și intergen în evoluţia utopiei literare</p>
<p>Daniela Tononi, Università degli Studi di Palermo: Le genre est-il un paradoxe ? La transgression générique dans « 53 jours » de Georges Perec</p>
<p>Karin Zotzmann, Universidad de Querétaro: Genre and Genre Change: A Critical Realist View</p>
<p>Open section:<br />
Réda Bensmaïa, Brown University: Le syndrome « Deleuze-Postcolonie » ou des noms  de Deleuze</p>
<p>Frank Jablonka, Antenne Universitaire de Beauvais: L’identité nationale à la lumière de l’immigration postcoloniale et son expression symbolique dans le hip-hop</p>
<p>Sandra Ponzanesi, Universiteit Utrecht: Mediterranean Routes: Migration Literature in Italy in a Postcolonial Perspective</p>
<p>Xosé Soto Andión, Universidade de Vigo: Construcciones intransitivas de caracterización en gallego: entre la atribución y la predicación</p>
<p>Dominique J.M. Soulas de Russel, Eberhard-Karls-Universität Tübingen: La « decolonisation» de l’enseigmenet du français en Afrique noire francophone. Par la contextualisation des textes pedagogiques</p></div>
